# Git workflow (agents propose, owner disposes)

Policy C: agents do real git work but the owner is the sole merge gatekeeper.
Source of truth: `docs/adr/0005-agent-git-governance-and-workflow.md` (when present).

- **Branch per feature:** `feat/<backlog-id>-<slug>` (e.g. `feat/PROJ-1-user-auth`).
  One feature per branch/session.
- **Conventional Commits** (`feat:`, `fix:`, `docs:`, `chore:`, `ci:`, …);
  commitlint enforces this when wired. Reference the backlog ID in the commit/PR.
- **Never push to or merge into `main`.** Push your feature branch and open a PR;
  the owner reviews and merges. Use client-side hooks when present; do not bypass
  them with `--no-verify` unless the user explicitly asks.
- **No commits or PRs without owner permission.** Do not run `git commit`,
  `git push`, or `gh pr create` unless the owner explicitly asks — typically after
  your session-end summary. Propose the commit message and PR body first; wait for
  approval before executing.
